13/01/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Wednesday (January 12th) that a small bomb exploded in Thessaloniki, damaging the office of a right-wing lawmaker and injuring one person. 
The blast, rigged out of canisters of cooking gas, happened in the centre of Thessaloniki outside the office of LAOS lawmaker Angelos Kolokotronis. 
A second bomb exploded minutes later outside the office of an association for retired police officers, causing minor damage and no injuries. 
(AP, ANA-MPA - 12/01/11)
